Types of volumes
  Named Volume: These are the docker manage volume with specific user defined name that docker handles the creations and the storage location is on the host typically within the system
        path: /var/lib/docker/<volume-name>/_data
        cmd: docker volum create <volume-name>
        example: docker run -itd --name myapp -v <volume-name>:/app ubuntu

 Bind Mounts: It is a another way to give your containers access to files and folders on your host. Its typically your host directory that you directly mount to your container
     mkdir app --> :/app any changes that you do in your systems app directory that directly reflects in the container directory
         1) creat directory -- any name -- changes
         2) docker container run -it -- name test -v /champu/:/app ubuntu
Anonymous volume: No mount point and host path needed its temp volume that create
    example: docker run -v /salman -- randomid
